Material Information Summary:

  • Key Partnership & Technology Breakthrough:
  • Signed MoU with MTM Critical Metals (ASX: MTM) to apply Flash Joule Heating (FJH) technology for rare earth element (REE) separation.

  • FJH Success:

    • Recovered 76% Pr, 65% Nd, 75% Dy, and 81% Tb from Meteoric’s MREC feedstock.
    • Removed 83% of low-value Lanthanum (La), increasing magnetic REO content from ~30% to 72% of TREO.

  • Strategic Impact:

  • Potential scalable, modular REE refining alternative, reducing reliance on China-dominated supply chains.

  • Pilot plant development planned (Poços de Caldas, Brazil) by September 2025, potentially hosting FJH demo facility.

  • Exclusivity:

  • MTM barred from similar Brazil-based ionic clay projects with third parties during the 12-month MoU term.

  • Next Steps:

  • Further FJH optimization to improve recovery rates and reject low-value elements (e.g., Cerium).

No capital raising, financials, or dated material events identified.

Material Information Summary (Farm-In & Joint Venture Agreement)

Key Deal Terms:

  • Farm-In Structure: Dart Mining (via subsidiary) to earn 51% interest in Coonambula Antimony-Gold Project (6 tenements, QLD) through staged investment:
  • Stage 1 (15%): Immediate payment of A$250,000 to Great Divide Mining (ASX:GDM).
  • Stage 2 (up to 36%): Earn additional interest via:
    • Drilling: 1% interest per 133.3m drilled (min. 4,000m total within 26 months).
    • Resource Reporting: 3% interest per annual JORC resource/exploration target (max. 6%).

Project Highlights:

  • High-Grade Potential: Historic drilling/trenching results include:
  • 3m @ 9.18% Sb + 20% Sb (1m); 6m @ 5.12% Sb + 1.55g/t Au.
  • Surface rock chips up to 44.9% Sb.
  • Near-Term Catalysts:
  • IP Survey (funded by QLD govt grant): 15-line km survey (starting within 3 months) to guide 2025 drilling.
  • Infill Drilling (Year 1): 2,000m targeting JORC resource declaration at Banshee mine.

Strategic Context:

  • Analogues: Comparable to Hillgrove Antimony-Gold Mine (ASX:LRV).
  • Location: Proximal to multi-million-ounce gold deposits (e.g., Cracow mine).
